Welcome to MkDocs


For full documentation visit 
mkdocs.org
.


Commands




mkdocs new [dir-name]
 - Create a new project.


mkdocs serve
 - Start the live-reloading docs server.


mkdocs build
 - Build the documentation site.


mkdocs help
 - Print this help message.




Project layout


mkdocs.yml    # The configuration file.
docs/
    index.md  # The documentation homepage.
    About.md  # test new page
    ...       # Other markdown pages, images and other files.

Create a Repository
From scratch -- Create a new local
repository
$ git init [project name]
Download from an existing repository
$ git clone my_url

fff





Setup


Show current configuration:


$ git config --list




Show repository configuration:


$ git config --local --list




Show global configuration:


$ git config --global --list





Show system configuration:


$ git config --system --list







Create


Clone an existing repository:


There are two ways:


Via SSH


$ git clone ssh://user@domain.com/repo.git




Via HTTP


$ git clone http://domain.com/user/repo.git




Create a new local repository:


$ git init

Welcome to gitflow


Installing on Windows


Cygwin


For Windows users who wish to use the automated install, it is suggested that you install 
Cygwin

first to install tools like 
git
, 
util-linux
 and 
wget
 (with those three being packages that can be selected
during installation). Then simply run this command from a Cygwin shell in your 
$HOME
:


$ wget -q -O - --no-check-certificate https://github.com/nvie/gitflow/raw/develop/contrib/gitflow-installer.sh stable

started new feature
